Christmas night, 1996.  Thirty years ago tonight I was acting CQ for someone who needed to go home to be with family in Rhode Island. I was CQ at the Armed Forces Institute of Pathology down on The Mall where today the Hirshorn Museum stands.<br>
The AFIP Museum held such oddities as the &quot;pickled babies&quot; and the forensic curiosities from the American Civil War<br>
as well as the most complete microscope collection in the world.  From that perspective, Christmas Night, 1966, I saw and then slept <br>
a vast correspondence with understanding the way this earth <br>
still spins.<br><br>
Merry Christmas...we really do deserve it.
